00:54:00.449 --> 00:54:01.490
AUDIENCE: Quick question.

00:54:01.490 --> 00:54:04.890
I heard someone say
somewhere that all humor is

00:54:04.890 --> 00:54:06.550
subversive at the heart of it.

00:54:06.550 --> 00:54:09.875
You mentioned that you as
a child were subversive.

00:54:09.875 --> 00:54:12.280
And I just wanted to
get your take on that.

00:54:12.280 --> 00:54:14.180
JOHN CLEESE: Yes I
think, I'll tell you

00:54:14.180 --> 00:54:18.090
why I think--
there's two reasons.

00:54:18.090 --> 00:54:21.450
The first one is
that people who are

00:54:21.450 --> 00:54:24.240
very pompous and
authoritarian, they

00:54:24.240 --> 00:54:27.920
have organizations, which stamp
out any kind of criticism.

00:54:27.920 --> 00:54:31.260
You know, people
are terrified to say

00:54:31.260 --> 00:54:34.006
what they think because
if they really disagree

00:54:34.006 --> 00:54:35.880
with the people in
charge, they're in trouble

00:54:35.880 --> 00:54:37.500
and they may get fired.

00:54:37.500 --> 00:54:42.610
Now in places like that, and it
was a bit like that in the USSR

00:54:42.610 --> 00:54:45.110
not so long ago,
then the only way

00:54:45.110 --> 00:54:49.540
that people could express
criticism or discontent

00:54:49.540 --> 00:54:50.630
was through humor.

00:54:50.630 --> 00:54:52.470
They could make jokes.

00:54:52.470 --> 00:54:54.650
So the ones, the
people in charge,

00:54:54.650 --> 00:54:58.580
saw jokes as subversive,
as subverting

00:54:58.580 --> 00:55:01.260
the system, the
power system, which

00:55:01.260 --> 00:55:02.570
gave them all their power.

00:55:02.570 --> 00:55:06.470
So they kind of dismissed
humor as subversive.

00:55:06.470 --> 00:55:09.785
And there's a certain kind
of very puritanical mind

00:55:09.785 --> 00:55:12.060
that mistrusts humor.

00:55:12.060 --> 00:55:15.020
There was a famous case
of somebody working

00:55:15.020 --> 00:55:20.670
for Henry Ford in a factory
called the Red River Factory.

00:55:20.670 --> 00:55:23.460
I don't know where Red River is.

00:55:23.460 --> 00:55:28.080
But there was a guy there
who was fired for laughing.

00:55:28.080 --> 00:55:31.100
And then there was
an inquiry about why.

00:55:31.100 --> 00:55:36.140
He had been warned the
previous month for smiling.

00:55:36.140 --> 00:55:39.110
So when you get people
who are absolutely

00:55:39.110 --> 00:55:43.850
obsessional about doing
things, then any kind of humor

00:55:43.850 --> 00:55:48.020
is a threat to that
obsessional pursuit of a goal.

00:55:48.020 --> 00:55:50.030
You can imagine
that there were not

00:55:50.030 --> 00:55:54.410
a lot of jokes going
around Himmler's SS.

00:55:54.410 --> 00:55:56.420
Do you see what I mean?

00:55:56.420 --> 00:56:00.240
But if you look at humor,
it's really about two things.

00:56:00.240 --> 00:56:04.270
If you laugh at a
character in a comedy,

00:56:04.270 --> 00:56:08.520
it's always because
he is not, he's

00:56:08.520 --> 00:56:10.890
not behaving appropriately.

00:56:10.890 --> 00:56:16.130
It's only inappropriate
behavior that could be funny.

00:56:16.130 --> 00:56:19.940
Similarly, comedy is
about things going wrong.

00:56:19.940 --> 00:56:23.790
If somebody goes
off on a journey,

00:56:23.790 --> 00:56:26.370
and everything goes right,
there's nothing funny.

00:56:26.370 --> 00:56:29.760
It starts getting funny
when things go wrong.

00:56:29.760 --> 00:56:31.850
So that means that
people are funny when

00:56:31.850 --> 00:56:35.430
they're inappropriate and things
are funny when they go wrong.

00:56:35.430 --> 00:56:37.980
So there's
essentially something,

00:56:37.980 --> 00:56:39.860
when we laugh that's critical.

00:56:39.860 --> 00:56:40.360
You know.

00:56:40.360 --> 00:56:42.790
We're laughing at someone
because they're not

00:56:42.790 --> 00:56:45.840
behaving appropriately or
because they screwed up

00:56:45.840 --> 00:56:47.190
and so things are going wrong.

00:56:47.190 --> 00:56:48.100
You see what I mean?

00:56:48.100 --> 00:56:53.330
So there's an element-- It is
true to say that all humor is,

00:56:53.330 --> 00:56:56.080
in some very subtle
way, critical.

00:56:56.080 --> 00:56:59.590
Because if you have somebody
whose life is going smoothly

00:56:59.590 --> 00:57:01.230
and who is behaving
appropriately,

00:57:01.230 --> 00:57:04.080
there's no way you
could make them funny.

00:57:04.080 --> 00:57:07.360
But that's a little different
from the subversive attitude.

00:57:07.360 --> 00:57:09.690
OK?

00:57:09.690 --> 00:57:11.190
