00:59:09.100 --> 00:59:11.620
if I think-- I have
a feeling that if I'd

00:59:11.620 --> 00:59:16.820
tried to write a novel, I
don't think I could do it.

00:59:16.820 --> 00:59:17.910
I don't know why.

00:59:17.910 --> 00:59:21.640
I just don't feel that my
skills would extend to that.

00:59:21.640 --> 00:59:25.250
But because I've written
for television and film

00:59:25.250 --> 00:59:29.326
all my life, it's natural
for me to write dialogue.

00:59:29.326 --> 00:59:30.950
So I knew I'd be able
to write dialogue

00:59:30.950 --> 00:59:33.650
but I didn't know if I'd
be able to write narrative.

00:59:33.650 --> 00:59:36.690
And all I did was, whenever
I wrote a sentence,

00:59:36.690 --> 00:59:39.430
I read it out as though
it was a line of dialogue,

00:59:39.430 --> 00:59:41.060
even when it was narrative.

00:59:41.060 --> 00:59:44.450
And I just found that if it
sounded right, I left it.

00:59:44.450 --> 00:59:48.370
And if it didn't sound
right, and you guys in IT

00:59:48.370 --> 00:59:51.110
will be delighted to know
that I wrote with a propelling

00:59:51.110 --> 00:59:54.860
pencil in an exercise book.

00:59:54.860 --> 00:59:56.620
And I loved the contact.

00:59:56.620 --> 00:59:59.700
And I would just keep
on rubbing out that line

00:59:59.700 --> 01:00:05.480
and writing it until it sounded
right when I read it out.

01:00:05.480 --> 01:00:08.540
And my editor, who did
an extraordinary job,

01:00:08.540 --> 01:00:10.900
he said, and I'd never
have guessed this,

01:00:10.900 --> 01:00:14.910
he said the vast majority of
writers are fine on narrative

01:00:14.910 --> 01:00:19.110
and can't do dialogue
to save their lives.

01:00:19.110 --> 01:00:20.620
So I started the
other way round,

01:00:20.620 --> 01:00:22.410
and found that actually
writing in the narrative

01:00:22.410 --> 01:00:23.270
was not difficult.

01:00:23.270 --> 01:00:25.270
But that was because I
just was listening to it.

01:00:25.270 --> 01:00:27.690
And the nicest thing people
have said about the book

01:00:27.690 --> 01:00:30.190
is that it's like having a
dinner conversation with me.

01:00:30.190 --> 01:00:32.730
They can hear my voice.

01:00:32.730 --> 01:00:35.301
So I was surprised to
find that, but pleased.

01:00:35.301 --> 01:00:36.092
AUDIENCE: Right on.

01:00:36.092 --> 01:00:36.510
Thank you.

01:00:36.510 --> 01:00:37.160
